cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.PL 

This paper deals with materialisation of datalog rules, which is a core topic in database systems (cs.DB). It also proposes a modular framework for handling datalog programs, which involves reasoning and computation, making it relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses algorithms for computing transitive and symmetric-transitive closures, which are topics in logic (cs.LO) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with the implementation of datalog programs, which is a topic in programming languages (cs.PL).
